                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430227-1053-offence-1 t18430227-name-1231"></join>Joseph Wing Arnold</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1232" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1232" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1232" type="surname" value="ARNOLD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1232" type="given" value="JOSEPH WING"></interp>JOSEPH WING ARNOLD</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Long-acre, and deal in hams. A little before six o'clock on the 27th of Feb. I saw a ham safe in my window—I missed it soon after—I have not found it.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184302270220"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1233" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1233" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1233" type="surname" value="TINKIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1233" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE TINKIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I was standing opposite the prosecutor's shop, and I saw a woman go to the end of the shop—the prisoner came and joined her—they then went into the shop—the prisoner took the ham and came out—they came past me, and the prisoner gave the ham to another man—I ran and took the prisoner, but the other man got off with it—I went and told the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He says he never lost sight of me, and yet he went into the shop. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> They walked very deliberately along till they saw me, and then he gave the ham to the other man—the prisoner popped into Broad-court, and ran into the pawnbroker's, and I after him—he did not say what he wanted; the pawnbroker asked him, and he said, "I want a fustian jacket."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I went into the pawnbroker's to buy a jacket; the witness came in and accused me of the ham; I said, "You must be mistaken, I have not been so far as the shop."</p>
               <p>
